Key Match Events: Zebby Matthews allowed 9 runs in 2 innings, the second time this week a Twins pitcher has done so
The Blue Jays scored 7 runs in the first inning
Addison Barger hit a two-run home run
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Twins allowed 23 hits, their most in a game since 2011
All relevant teams around them in the AL Central and AL Wild Card standings all lost
Others: Rocco Baldelli mentioned that Matthews has a lot to learn from the experience
Matthews threw strikes and got 12 swinging strikes but his mistakes got hit hard
Baldelli mentioned that Matthews will have a next time to pitch
